<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-09-18T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-09-18T18:00:00-05:00" n="1084" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1084">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/1378</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Mr. <persName type="to">Parker</persName>, representing American
                                interests</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-09-18T18:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 18, 1916, 6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>423. Department informed that recent Carranza decree requires repayment
                            of taxes paid Villa in territory controlled by Villa faction. Matter
                            brought Department’s attention by American citizens interested in
                            property in State of Nuevo Leon. Investigate and forward copy of decree
                            if issued.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>